link-grammar
------------------------------------------
The Link Grammar Parser is a syntactic parser of English, based on link 
grammar, an original theory of English syntax. Given a sentence, the 
system assigns to it a syntactic structure, which consists of a set of 
labeled links connecting pairs of words. The parser also produces a 
'constituent' representation of a sentence (showing noun phrases, verb 
phrases, etc.).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.5-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libaspell15-0.60.5-1

Build requirements:
  autoconf2.5-2.63-1
  automake1.10-1.10.3-1
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.9.84-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.2.7b-15
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10

Canonical website:
  http://www.link.cs.cmu.edu/link/

Canonical download:
  http://www.abisource.com/downloads/link-grammar/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack link-grammar-4.6.7-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./link-grammar-4.6.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/liblink-grammar-devel-4.6.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/liblink-grammar4-4.6.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/link-grammar-4.6.7-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/link-grammar-4.6.7-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

